\"ISic003391_context_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_context.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(House of) Gnaius Modius\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Archaeologically, the 'baths of Cnaius Modius' (so called because of this inscription at the entrance) should be dated to the first century BC (so Tréziny 2018: 274), not the third-century BC as discussed in Torelli 2007\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2007.0671 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 59.1107 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 26.1102 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1975 152 no.18 tav.34.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Torelli 2007 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tréziny 2018 273-274 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Letters neatly formed of small black basalt stone chips. Nu has a shorter right hand vertical; omicron is equal size to the other letters; alpha off vertical, cross-bar formed by single piece; mu formed by four equal off-vertical strokes, mid-point descending fully to the base-line.\u003C/p> Line 1 \u003Cp> Types list: \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Δ type2\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2.1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1.2\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/typ